=== HARNESS FORMAT (READ THIS CAREFULLY) ===
The libFuzzer harness does this with your bytes:

```cpp
{{ harness_code }}
```

Your bytes will be fed DIRECTLY to `hb_blob_create(data, size)`, then
`hb_face_create(blob, 0)` → `hb_font_create(face)` → `hb_shape(font, buffer, NULL, 0)`.

**YOUR JOB**: produce base64-encoded bytes representing a font blob.
You do NOT need a fully valid font. Partial tables, truncated headers,
and deliberately malformed features are all useful if they exercise
specific code paths. The harness silently ignores crashes.
**Keep each blob TINY (≤ 64 bytes, HARD LIMIT)**. Harfbuzz parses headers
first, so a 12–64 byte sfnt stub exercises multiple parse paths. A 64-byte
blob base64-encodes to exactly 88 characters — stay under that.

**OUTPUT FORMAT**: each `content_b64` must be standard base64 of the RAW
BYTES you want fed to hb_blob_create. Do NOT base64-encode text. Do NOT
output hex strings. Output BINARY bytes encoded as base64.
